      • createChainedIterator

        public static <E> Iterator<E> createChainedIterator(Collection<? extends Iterator<E>> iterators)
        Create a new Iterator instance that wraps several Iterators behind a single Iterator instance. Once all the elements in the first iterator have been iterated over, the next iterator in the chain gets used.
        Returns:
        a new Iterator instance; never null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the input collection is null or if any element in the collection is null.

      • createChainedStreamingIterator

        public static <E> StreamingIterator<E> createChainedStreamingIterator(Collection<? extends StreamingIterator<? extends E>> iterators)
        Create a new StreamingIterator instance that wraps several StreamingIterators behind a single StreamingIterator instance. Once all the elements in the first iterator have been iterated over, the next iterator in the chain gets used. If at any time, StreamingIterator.close() is called, then all downstream StreamingIterator are closed as well.
        Returns:
        a new StreamingIterator instance; never null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the input collection is null or if any element in the collection is null.

      • rollover

        public static <T,L extends List<T> & RandomAccess> Iterator<T> rollover(L randomAccessList)
        Create a new Iterator that will iterate over the given list and start over again when it reaches the end of the list. This iterator will never end if the list is not empty.
        Parameters:
        randomAccessList - a list that implements the RandomAccess marker interface.
        Returns:
        a new Iterator that starts at the beginning of the list.
        Since:
        5.3

      • rollover

        public static <T,L extends List<T> & RandomAccess> Iterator<T> rollover(L randomAccessList,
                                                                        int startOffset)
        Create a new Iterator that will iterate over the given list and start over again when it reaches the end of the list. This iterator will never end if the list is not empty.
        Parameters:
        randomAccessList - a list that implements the RandomAccess marker interface.
        startOffset - the offset to start iterating from. If this value is beyond the list size, then the start location will roll over accordingly.
        Returns:
        a new Iterator that starts at the specified offset.
        Since:
        5.3
